      <bioghist id="aspace_9fbc84e09d86648498e367af4732c10b">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Mirjan R. Damaška received his LL.B. at the University of Zagreb, Croatia, and his Dr. Jur. at the University of Ljubljana, Slovenia, in 1960. He began his teaching career at the University of Zagreb Law School.  In 1971, he left Croatia to accept a position at the University of Pennsylvania Law School.  Damaška joined the Yale Law School faculty in 1976 and is Sterling Professor Emeritus of Law and Professorial Lecturer in Law. He has served as advisor to the Croatian government in its relations with the International War Crimes Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia, and the International Court of Justice in The Hague since 1995.</p>
         <p>Biographical information found on Yale Law School website.</p>  
      </bioghist>
